    <stitle>13 SPEED AND 18 SPEED TRANSMISSIONS EATON RTLO-713/18 SERIES - INSTALL - AIR LINES AND HOSE</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="install" graphiccount="2">
        <title>AIR LINES AND HOSE</title>
        <specpara>
            <note>
                <para>Make sure air lines and hose are not damaged.</para>
            </note>
        </specpara>
        <specpara>
            <note>
                <para>Install the air lines and hose at their proper location.</para>
            </note>
        </specpara>
        <specpara>
            <note>
                <para>All externally threaded 1/8" or 5/32" air lines and pipe fittings that are not coated with
                    pre-applied thread sealant must be coated with Eaton sealing material #71209 or Loctite 242 for at
                    least 5 complete and consecutive threads.
                </para>
            </note>
        </specpara>
        <specpara>
            <note>
                <para>All externally threaded 1/4" air fittings that are not coated with pre-applied thread sealant must
                    be coated with Eaton sealing material #71209 or Loctite 242 for at least 3 complete and consecutive
                    threads.
                </para>
            </note>
        </specpara>
        <specpara>
            <note>
                <para>For the 1/4" I.D. air hoses, install the fixed nut end first.</para>
            </note>
        </specpara>
        <specpara>
            <note>
                <para>To install the air lines and hose, the air filter/regulator must be in position.</para>
            </note>
        </specpara>
        <specpara>
            <note>
                <para>For "push-to-connect" fittings, we recommend Eaton service tool kit K-2394. The kit contains the
                    release tool and a tubing cutter.
                </para>
            </note>
        </specpara>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Replace removed air fittings (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13007s0">Figure 280</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f13007s0" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g13007s0" filename="../figg13/G13007s0.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
                <caption>Figure 280. Replace Removed Air Fittings</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Connect all removed air lines and hoses (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13007s0">Figure 280</hotlnk>and
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13007s1">Figure 281</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f13007s1" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g13007s1" filename="../figg13/G13007s1.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
                <caption>Figure 281. Connect All Removed Air Lines and Hoses</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
